        <h2 class="west-stand">
            John Charles (West) Stand:
        </h2>
        <img class="img-west-stand" image goes here>
        <p class="west-stand">
            
The John Charles West Stand at Elland Road honors the Welsh footballing legend and accommodates
 general admission and season ticket holders. Away fans are housed on one side of the stand, 
 towards the South Stand, with a normal allocation of 1,566 seats in the upper tier. If required, 
 an additional 1,104 seats can be provided in the lower tier, making the overall allocation 2,670.
  Offering panoramic views of the pitch, the West Stand provides modern amenities such as 
  concession stands and accessible seating areas. With its comfortable facilities and lively 
  atmosphere, the West Stand enhances the matchday experience for fans, contributing to the 
  rich history and identity of Elland Road.
        </p>
    </article>

    <article>
        <h2 class="east-stand">
            Jack Charlton (East) Stand:   
        </h2>
        <img class="img-east-stand"image goes here>
        <p class="east-stand">
            
The Jack Charlton East Stand at Elland Road is named in honor of the Leeds United and 
England legend, Jack Charlton. Formerly known as the Lowfields Road stand, it underwent 
renovations and was officially renamed to commemorate Charlton's contributions to the club's 
history. The East Stand provides corporate hospitality suites, executive boxes, and media 
facilities, catering to VIP guests and special events. It offers a premium matchday experience 
with modern amenities and excellent views of the pitch. The stand's spacious layout and 
comfortable facilities make it a popular choice for fans looking to enjoy the game in style. 
As an iconic part of Elland Road, the Jack Charlton East Stand adds to the stadium's rich 
heritage and provides a fitting tribute to one of Leeds United's greatest players.
        </p>
    </article>

    <article>
        <h2 class="billy">
            The Billy Bremner Statue:
        </h2>
        <img image goes here>
        <p class="billy">
            
The Billy Bremner Statue is a bronze sculpture located outside Elland Road Stadium, 
home to Leeds United Football Club. It commemorates the club's legendary captain, Billy Bremner, 
who played a pivotal role in the team's success during the 1960s and 1970s. Unveiled in 1999, 
the statue stands as a lasting tribute to Bremner's contributions to Leeds United and the sport 
of football as a whole. Positioned near the main entrance of the stadium, the statue serves as 
a focal point for fans, providing a place for reflection and remembrance of one of the club's
 most iconic figures. Visitors to Elland Road often take photographs with the statue, paying 
 homage to Bremner's legacy and the enduring spirit of Leeds United.
        </p>
    </article>

    <article>
        <h2 class="c-sqaure">
         Centenary Sqaure
        </h2>
        <img image goes here>
        <p class=c-sqaure>
         
Centenary Square at Elland Road, established for Leeds United's 100th anniversary in 2019, 
celebrates the club's rich history and legacy. Located near the stadium entrance, the square
 features commemorative plaques honoring legendary players and managers like Don Revie and
  Marcelo Bielsa. Itâ€™s a vibrant gathering place for fans on matchdays, filled with excitement
   and shared passion. Centenary Square not only reflects on the past but also symbolizes the
    club's enduring legacy and bright future, making it a must-visit for all supporters and
     visitors to Elland Road.


        </p>
    </article>
 
    <article>
        <h2 class="megastore">
            The Leeds United Megastore: 
        </h2>
        <img image goes here>
        <p class="megastore">
            
The Leeds United Megastore is the official retail outlet located within Elland Road Stadium, 
serving as a hub for fans to purchase a wide range of club merchandise and memorabilia. 
Boasting an extensive selection of apparel, accessories, and souvenirs, the megastore offers 
supporters the opportunity to show their allegiance to the club in style. From replica jerseys
 and scarves to novelty items and gifts, the store caters to fans of all ages and preferences. 
 Staffed by friendly and knowledgeable personnel, the megastore provides a welcoming shopping 
 experience for visitors to Elland Road, whether they're attending a match or simply exploring 
 the stadium. As a key destination for Leeds United enthusiasts, the megastore plays an essential 
 role in connecting fans with the club's identity and heritage.
        </p>
    </article>

    <article>
        <h2 class="mural">
            The South Stand Mural: 
        </h2>
        <img image goes here>
        <p class="mural">
         
The South Stand Mural at Elland Road Stadium is a vibrant artwork that adorns the walls of the
 stand, capturing iconic moments and symbols of Leeds United's history and identity. Stretching 
 across the interior of the South Stand, the mural serves as a visual celebration of the club's
  rich heritage, featuring depictions of legendary players, memorable matches, and emblematic 
  imagery associated with Leeds United. Designed to inspire and captivate fans, the mural
   contributes to the electric atmosphere of matchdays, creating a sense of pride and belonging 
   among supporters. As a prominent feature of Elland Road, the South Stand Mural serves as a
    powerful reminder of the club's legacy and the passion of its dedicated fanbase.   
        </p>
    </article>